xmrig
------------------------------------------
XMRig High performance, open source, cross platform RandomX, CryptoNight and
Argon2 CPU/GPU miner, with official support for Windows.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libhwloc15-2.0.3-1
  libssl1.1-1.1.1d-1
  libuv1-1.32.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/xmrig/xmrig

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/xmrig/xmrig/archive/v5.5.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack xmrig-5.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./xmrig-5.5.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/xmrig-5.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/xmrig-5.5.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(xmrig)
  /usr/bin/xmrig.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/xmrig.README
  /usr/share/doc/xmrig/ChangeLog.md
  /usr/share/doc/xmrig/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/xmrig/README.md
  /usr/share/xmrig/config.json

------------------

